The paper proposes a new geometric shaping design for golden angle modulation (GAM) targeting future generation cellular, microwave-links, or optical fiber systems. The paper focuses on improving the mutual information (MI) and the peak-to-average power ratio over the full signal-to-noise ratio (SNR) range. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Communications (cs.COMM), Signal Processing (cs.SI), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Physics (cs.PHY) sub-categories.
